=== Microsoft Research Collaboration - #styled-link("https://www.linkedin.com/posts/manishsgupta_microsoft-india-datascience-activity-7081315392941412352-9fhY")[MAPG 2023]

Earned *Microsoft Academic Partnership Grant (MAPG)* for research on neural network optimization. Collaborated with MSR India scientists to develop *quaternion transformers* using the *lottery ticket hypothesis*, maintaining performance with 2–4 times fewer weights. This research led to *two publications* in the Northern Lights Deep Learning Conference.

// Section 1: Promoted to the top. This is the single most relevant item.
=== MSc Thesis: ML for Computational Physics

- Reduced time complexity from $O(n^3)$ to $O(n)$ in #styled-link("https://peithonking.github.io/Aritra_Mukhopadhyay_MSc_Thesis.pdf")[MSc thesis] by training generative ML models (GANs, Diffusion) to estimate lattice energies with $<3\%$ error, directly bypassing expensive many-body computations.
- Investigated framework extension to semi-classical/quantum systems, identifying the core challenges for applying ML to many-body problems.

// Section 3: Promoted. "Moiré lattices" is highly relevant to the condensed matter field.
=== MoirePy – Python Library - #styled-link("https://pypi.org/project/MoirePy/")[PyPI], #styled-link("https://github.com/jabed-umar/MoirePy/")[GitHub]

Authored `MoirePy`, a FOSS Python library for simulating bilayer moiré lattices; published in beta stage on PyPI. Designed and implemented all code, CI/CD, packaging and documentation end to end on GitHub.

